=09=09=09=09General Electric, an American conglomerate, announced a friendl=
y takeover of=20
another American giant, Honeywell International, that will be worth $43=20
billion. The merger heads off a bid by United Technologies, an aerospace an=
d=20
appliance firm that hoped to boost its business in aircraft engines. GE chi=
ef=20
Jack Welch, who had been scheduled to retire next April, will stay until th=
e=20
end of 2001 to oversee the merging of the companies.
