w his tenure=20
end unexpectedly early. Two weeks after declaring his intent to stay with t=
he=20
company, Mr McGinn was sacked by a hostile board. The move followed a 10%=
=20
drop on last year in Lucent=01,s annual profits.
=09=09=09=09See article: Troubled Lucent ditches its bossE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09ABB, a leading engineering firm, has lost its chief executive. =
After 30 years=20
with the company and four years in the top job, G"ran Lindahl stepped down =
in=20
the wake of poor third-quarter figures, saying it was time to hand it over=
=20
=01&to a younger leader with a true IT profile=018. His successor will be J=
"rgen=20
Centerman, head of ABB=01,s automation division.
=09=09=09=09
